data.text:
Münster of Bern, Bern, Switzerland

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 46.947456, 7.451123.

Münster of Bern (Münstergasse) is an old historic Gothic cathedral located in the city of Bern in Switzerland. With the bell tower being close to 100 meters tall, the cathedral is one of the tallest religious establishments in the country. The construction of the cathedral lasted for over 400 years, with the finalizing of the bell tower in the late 19th century. Today it is one of the most favorite tourist attractions of the city, and those who come to the cathedral usually climb up to the bell tower to get to what is known as Münsterplattform (Minster Terrace) and enjoy the amazing view to the city and the neighborhood.
